91b7%5C%22%3ETravelers%20are%20scrambling%20to%20find%20a%20backup%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStranded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflights-delayed-canceled-travel-plans-what-to-do%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etravelers%20have%20few%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20depart%20Caribbean%20nations%20%E2%80%94%20and%20little%20help%20from%20airlines%20while%20they%20wait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20disruptions%20stem%20from%20government%20action%20outside%20the%20airlines'%20control%2C%20carriers%20do%20not%20legally%20owe%20passengers%20compensation.%20That%20means%20meals%2C%20hotels%2C%20and%20ground%20transportation%20are%20not%20required%20under%20federal%20law%2C%20though%20airlines%20may%20offer%20assistance%20as%20a%20gesture%20of%20goodwill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20X%20user%20who%20goes%20by%20Nate_F_Thurmond%20posted%20a%20photo%20of%20a%20group%20of%20stranded%20travelers%20in%20St.%20John.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPassengers%20stranded%20in%20St%20John%20just%20learning%20that%20Caribbean%20Airspace%20is%20closed%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAmerican%2C%20JetBlue%2C%20and%20Delta%20canceled%20flights.%20People%20are%20scrambling%20to%20find%20places%20to%20stay.%20Being%20told%203-5%20days%20by%20the%20airlines.%20All%20this%20because%20of%20Venezuela%3F%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20cases%2C%20the%20only%20guaranteed%20option%20is%20rebooking%2C%20and%20travelers%20may%20struggle%20to%20find%20alternative%20accommodations%20while%20waiting%20for%20the%20next%20available%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20flights%20are%20still%20operating%2C%20but%20they%20are%20taking%20significant%20detours%20to%20avoid%20the%20region.%20American%20Airlines%20Flight%201512%20from%20Georgetown%2C%20Guyana%2C%20to%20Miami%20on%20Saturday%2C%20for%20example%2C%20ditched%20its%20usual%20route%20east%20of%20Venezuela%20through%20the%20southern%20Caribbean%20and%20instead%20flew%20west%20around%20the%20area%2C%20adding%20roughly