2563dc-ee7c-4ef8-a1d2-f198081ab6cf%5C%22%3EI%20moved%20from%20the%20US%20to%20Wales%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20adult%2C%20I%20moved%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-it-like-moving-from-the-us-to-the-uk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20to%20Wales%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20once%20again%2C%20had%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20fit%20in%20%E2%80%94%20through%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20invited%20myself%20to%20people's%20houses%20for%20coffee%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20go%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-travel-with-friends-without-losing-friendships-tips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewalks%20with%20me%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20texted%20and%20rang%20to%20check%20in%20on%20friends%20I%20had%20made%20through%20church%2C%20work%2C%20my%20kids'%20school%2C%20and%20my%20husband's%20previous%20social%20circles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20friends%20were%20incredibly%20important%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20them.%20I%20felt%20the%20only%20way%20to%20do%20this%20was%20to%20maintain%20frequent%20contact%2C%20more%20often%20than%20not%20initiated%20by%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20thinking%3A%20What%20would%20happen%20if%20I%20didn't%20text%2C%20call%2C%20or%20plan%20to%20meet%20up%20with%20friends%3F%20Would%20they%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20me%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20led%20to%20little%20monthlong%20experiments%20%E2%80%94%20going%20quiet%20to%20see%20who%20I'd%20hear%20from%2C%20if%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20have%20been%20both%20disappointing%20and%20frustrating%2C%20yet%20reaffirming.%20There%20were%20some%20friends%20who%20didn't%20make%20any%20contact%20(and%20I%20felt%20rejected%20as%20a%20result)%2C%20others%20who%20got%20in%20touch%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20my%20childhood%20fears%20about%20exclusion%20and%20rejection%20were%20acutely%20felt%20once%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2517c7a-0c8f-4114-821b-88a3d1485eec%5C%22%3EI'm%20a%20loyal%20friend%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20lots%20to%20think%20through.%20Did%20I%20mind%20being%20the%20one%20who%20initiated%20the%20friendship%20%E2%80%94%20the%20one%20who%20kept%20it%20going%3F%20Was%20my%20concept%20of%20friendship%20too%20intense%20for%20other%20people%3F%20Were%20there%20some%20friendships%20I%20was%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20the%20work%2C%20even%20if%20I%20felt%20it%20wasn't%20always%20reciprocated%3F%20Was%20I%20a%20needy%20friend%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20soul-searching%20led%20me%20to%20understand%20a%20few%20things%20about%20myself%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20loyal%20friend%20who%20values%20deep%2C%20meaningful%20relationships%20that%20require%20time%20and%20effort.%20I%20make%20space%20for%20close%20friends%2C%20even%20though%20I%20work%20full-time%2C%20am%20married%2C%20and%20have%20three%20children%2C%20and%20I%20crave%20friendships%20with%20people%20who%20share%20the%20same%20values.%20A%20twice-a-year%20check-in%20just%20doesn't%20do%20it%20for%20me.%20I%20want%20sisterhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20not%20necessarily%20a%20value%20that%20everyone%20else%20has%2C%20and%20that's%20OK.%20I%20suppose%20some%20people%20don't%20need%20such%20intense%20friendships.%20Or%20perhaps%20they%20already%20have%20them%20with%20family%20or%20other%20friends.%20I%20can't%20get%20frustrated%20with%20or%20feel%20rejected%20by%20friends%20who%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20idea%20of%20friendship%20as%20I%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20frustration%20and%20feelings%20of%20rejection%2C%20over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20I've%20decided%20to%20mentally%20note%20which%20friends%20want%20the%20depth%20of%20friendship%20I%20offer%20and%20those%20who%20are%20happy%20with%20a%20surface-level%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22089eb755-16ec-4887-b912-1d644be75fec%5C%22%3EI%20stopped%20chasing%20friends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20leaned%20into%20those%20deep%20friendships%20(three%20of%20them)%20%E2%80%94%20people%20who%20valued%20relationships%20as%20much%20as%20I%20did.%20They%20feel%20like%20my%20village%2C%20those%20who%20depend%20on%20me%2C%20and%20those%20who%20I%20can%20depend%20on.%20They're%20the%20ones%20who%20check%20in%20with%20me%2C%20just%20as%20I%20check%20in%20on%20them.%20It's%20not%20me%20who%20initiates%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20texting%20and%20calling%20too.%20They're%20fiercely%20loyal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20stopped%20chasing%20friends%20who%20didn't%20seem%20to%20place%20the%20same%20value%20on%20friendship%20as%20I%20do.%20I%20didn't%20cut%20them%20out%20(and%20would%20happily%20still%20see%20them%20for%20a%20coffee)%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20prioritize%20contact%20as%20I%20had%20before.%20I%20didn't%20feel%20any%20resentment%2C%20but%20rather%20an%20understanding%20that%20we%20had%20different%20ideas%20of%20what%20friendship%20entailed.%20And%20that's%20totally%20OK%20%E2%80%94%20I%20can%20accept%20this%20without%20feeling%20rejected%20or%20unwanted.%20When%20we%20do%20see%20each%20other%2C%20at%20school%20gates%2C%20on%20the%20streets%2C%20or%20for%20an%20infrequent%20meet-up%2C%20I%20enjoy%20their%20company%2C%20expecting%20no%20more%20than%20they%20are%20able%20to%20give.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20there%20were%20a%20couple%20of%20friends%20whom%20I%20knew%20I%20would%20have%20to%20initiate%20contact%20with%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20maintain%20our%20friendship%20%E2%80%94%20I'd%20have%20to%20accept%20that%20for%20it%20to%20continue.%20I%20appreciated%20their%20friendships%20too%20much%20to%20only%20see%20or%20hear%20from%20them%20occasionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20with%20these%20changes%20in%20place%2C%20I%20feel%20completely%20content%20in%20my%20friendships%2C%20as%20I%20have%20never%20before.%20I%20know%20where%20I%20stand%20with%20friends%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20don't%20feel%20rejected%20%E2%80%94%20no%20longer%20that%20child%20with%20an%20insatiable%20desire%20to%20be%20accepted%20by%20everyone.%20I%20know%20I'm%20wanted%20and%20loved%2C%20not%20by%20everyone%2C%20but%20by%20a%20few%2C%20and%20that's%20enough%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-stopped-chasing-friends-and-finally-found-loyal-friendships-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767472681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6936fe6d7ecd1d1da6631c0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-stopped-chasing-friends-and-finally-found-loyal-friendships-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pulling%20back%20from%20friendships%20showed%20me%20exactly%20who%20wanted%20me%20in%20their%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20finally%20quieted%20my%20lifelong%20fear%20of%20rejection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lauren%20Crosby%20Medlicott)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A92%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-stopped-chasing-friends-and-finally-found-loyal-friendships-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sara%20Arjun%20thanks%20%E2%80%98my%20strongest%20Dhurandhars%E2%80%99%20after%20success%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767472665000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-126327705%2Cimgsize-14492.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fsara-arjun-thanks-my-strongest-dhurandhars-after-dhurandhars-box-office-run-you-proved-audiences-still-believe-in-long-form-storytelling%2Farticleshow%2F126327703.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F126327703.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ESara%20Arjun%2C%20who%20made%20her%20debut%20as%2