h%20to%20parenting%20with%20the%20acronym%20TRICK.%20It%20stands%20for%20trust%2C%20respect%2C%20independence%2C%20collaboration%2C%20and%20kindness.%20Those%20are%20the%20tenets%20of%20great%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20parent%20trusts%20their%20child%20to%20do%20something%20%E2%80%94%20even%20as%20simple%20as%20making%20dessert%20%E2%80%94%20it%20empowers%20the%20kid.%20They%20feel%20better%20about%20themselves.%20They%20figure%20they're%20capable%2C%20because%20they've%20been%20trusted%20with%20a%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERespect%20goes%20both%20ways.%20Really%20listen%20to%20what%20the%20child%20has%20to%20say.%20Of%20course%2C%20you%20won't%20always%20do%20what%20they%20want%20as%20a%20parent%2C%20but%20at%20least%20talk%20a%20decision%20over%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndependence%20is%20something%20our%20kids%20need%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%20How%20can%20we%20expect%20to%20raise%20independent%20adults%20if%20we're%20always%20doing%20everything%20for%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollaboration%20is%20much%20better%20than%20dictating%20to%20children.%20When%20we%20collaborate%20with%20them%2C%20they%20have%20autonomy%2C%20and%20we're%20showing%20them%20trust.%20I%20saw%20firsthand%20in%20my%20classrooms%20that%20when%20students%20came%20up%20with%20the%20class%20rules%2C%20they%20were%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20follow%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20kindness.%20People%20might%20forget%20what%20you%20did%2C%20but%20they'll%20never%20forget%20how%20you%20made%20them%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22878cab51-bd7d-4f3c-9c3c-26768f04af14%5C%22%3EKids%20will%20make%20mistakes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20so%20will%20parents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20girls%20started%20making%20their%20own%20breakfast%20when%20they%20were%20toddlers.%20They%20would%20pull%20out%20the%20cereal%20and%20milk%2C%20which%20I%20kept%20in%20a%20small%20jug%20low%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%20them%20to%20reach.%20A%20mess%20would%20be%20all%20over%20the%20floor%2C%20but%20they%20loved%20making%20their%20own%20bowls%2C%20and%20I%20liked%20that%20I%20could%20sleep%20in%20a%20bit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20were%20older%2C%20they%20made%20their%20own%20sandwiches.%20You%20wouldn't%20believe%20how%20awful%20those%20sandwiches%20looked%2C%20but%20they%20were%20happy%20that%20they%20made%20their%20own%20lunches.%20They%20rode%20their%20bikes%20to%20swim%20practice%20alone%20and%20set%20up%20their%20own%20playdates.%20They%20were%20do-it-yourselfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20very%20different%20in%20today's%20world%3B%20I%20see%20that%20with%20my%2010%20grandchildren.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20culture%20of%20fear%2C%20worrying%20about%20kids%20getting%20kidnapped%20or%20another%20parent%20calling%20the%20police%20on%20us%20if%20we%20let%20our%20kids%20walk%20to%20school.%20Yet%20it's%20still%20so%20important%20to%20give%20our%20kids%20independence%20and%20space%20to%20make%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20the%20same%20as%20parents.%20You%20can't%20come%20up%20with%20a%20creative%20solution%20if%20you're%20always%20worried%20about%20whether%20you're%20doing%20it%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-esther-wojcicki-says-fail-fast-and-revise-works-parenting-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767454681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6930800504d0f0a114f1555d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-esther-wojcicki-says-fail-fast-and-revise-works-parenting-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Esther%20Wojcicki%20shares%20how%20her%20TRICK%20parenting%20method%20%E2%80%94%20trust%2C%20respect%2C%20independence%2C%20collaboration%2C%20and%20kindness%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20her%20raise%20successful%20kids.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com